    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Women's small writing tables with a cabinet at the back; often elaborately decorated and occasionally fitted for toilet purposes as well as writing.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000032081/Payne, 19th-Century European Furniture (1981)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Mesas de escritura pequeñas para mujeres con un gradin (gabinete) en la parte de atrás; a menudo decorado elaboradamente y ocasionalmente acondicionado para como tocador así como también para escribir.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
